context: The Assembly consisted of <a0_0><b5_0>nine<b5_0/><a0_0/> seats, with electors casting nine equal votes, of which no more than two could be given to any individual candidate. It is a method of voting called <a1_0><b6_0>a "weighted first past the post system"<b6_0/><a1_0/>. Four of the members of the Assembly formed the <a2_0><b7_0>Executive<b7_0/><a2_0/> Council, which devised policy and acted as an advisory body to the Administrator. The last Chief Minister of Norfolk Island was <a3_0><b8_0>Lisle Snell<b8_0/><a3_0/>. Other ministers included: <a4_0><b9_0>Minister for Tourism, Industry and Development<b9_0/><a4_0/>; Minister for Finance; Minister for Cultural Heritage and Community Services; and Minister for Environment.
